page.title: 04Highrise Buildings
page.content: On Tuesday we went up the inmarsat building which is the tallest building in our area. We looked North so we could see our school street but not our school because it was covered by houses. We saw Euston Station right below us because we were joined to Euston Tower. When we looked North we could see lots of secondary land use {park or grass}, in square seven we could see Gasholders, Camley Street, ST.Pancras gd, ST.Pancras hsp. In square nine we could see regents pk, Mosque. In square ten we could see Eversholt st, Euston Station. We could not see anything in square's 1,2,3,4,6, 8,11 or 12.
